<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="79d44f70-e2d0-503c-af94-d42c6b8258dd" activityNameId="611bd31f-901b-4627-998a-02f7a52001c8" parentActivityId="ba38e7d9-8e77-4033-94b7-bba4e71ae109" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1" energyValues="0">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">nuclear power plant construction, pressure water reactor, 1000MW</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en"/>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The module includes materials, energy and transport requirements used for construction of the plant. Land-use is included with the assumption of 40 years operation. Disposal of non-contaminated material from dismantling is also included, whereas contaminated materials are attributed to the operation.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The module is based on "nuclear power plant, pressure water reactor 1000MW", CH. Only difference is the supply mix of electricity, FR instead of CH.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]</text>
        </generalComment>
        <tag>ConvertedDataset</tag>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="252082de-7cec-4d38-a58f-2819f633c6b6">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">4220:Construction of utility projects</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <classification classificationId="f90efbb7-abb4-4996-9eae-1674196ab194">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">EcoSpold01Categories</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">nuclear power/power plants</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="0d751636-7d7e-11de-9ae2-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">FR</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Extrapolated from Swiss data on one specific plant.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The described plant Gösgen started commercial operation at the end of 1979. It belongs to the 1000 MW class. It has a Siemens designed primary circuit with three loop cooling, a spherical containment, and a cooling tower. This module can be assumed to be representative for French pressure water reactors of the same class.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="1979-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
