        <name xml:lang="en">diesel, burned in building machine</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">MJ</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Diesel used for construction and demolition. Around 6 million kg of diesel are used for construction of the plant. The energy demand for the demolition of a light-water nuclear power plant of the 1000 MW class is 75% of the amount of energy used for the construction of the NPP. Therefore, 6*10^6*(1 + 0.75) kg diesel. Source: ecoinvent v2 Report 6, part VII, p. 198).
The LHV of diesel is 42.8 MJ/kg (ecoinvent MasterData, accessed on 20230728).
&lt;The construction diesel consumption was added in 20230728; before only the demolition part was taken into account&gt;
